{"book": {"publisher": "FisicalBook", "synopsis": ""One must be superior to mankind in force, in loftiness of soul—in contempt’<br/>In these two devastating works, Nietzsche offers a sustained and often vitriolic attack on the morality and the beliefs of his time, in particular those of Hegel, Kant and Schopenhaur. Twilight of the Idols is a ‘grand declaration of war’ on reason, psychology and theology that combines highly charged personal attacks on his contemporaries with a lightning tour of his own philosophy. It also paves the way for The Anti-Christ, Nietzche’s final assault on institutional Christianity, in which he identifies himself with the ‘Dionysian’ artist and confronts Christ; the only opponent he feels worthy of him.<br/>In his introduction Michael Tanner discussed the themes of Nietzche’s argument and places the works in their historical and philosophical context.", "language": "en", "image": "https: //images.isbndb.com/covers/51/45/9780140445145.jpg", "title_long": "twilight-of-the-idols-and-the-antichrist", "edition": "Reissue", "dimensions": "Height: 7.77 Inches, Length: 5.06 Inches, Weight: 0.37037660016 Pounds, Width: 0.5 Inches", "dimensions_structured": {"length": {"unit": "inches", "value": 5.06}, "width": {"unit": "inches", "value": 0.5}, "weight": {"unit": "pounds", "value": 0.37037660016}, "height": {"unit": "inches", "value": 7.77}}, "pages": 208, "date_published": "1990", "subjects": ["Literature & Fiction', 'History & Criticism', 'Criticism & Theory', 'Politics & Social Sciences', 'Philosophy', 'Criticism', 'History & Surveys', 'Modern', 'Individual Philosophers'], 'authors": ["friedrich-nietzsche'], 'title": "twilight-of-the-idols-and-the-antichrist", "isbn13": "9780140445145", "msrp": 13, "binding": "Paperback", "isbn": "0140445145", "isbn10": "0140445145", "other_isbns": [{'isbn": "9780141904290", "binding": "printisbncanonical"}]}}